"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-06-paris-2024-olympics-brume-usoro-ochonogor-through-to-womens-long-jump-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Team Nigeria's trio of Ese Brume, Ruth Usoro and Prestina Ochonogor, have qualified for the women's long jump final at the ongoing 2024 Olympic Games.  It's the first time three Nigerian will be competing in the final of the long jump event at the Olympics.  The trio will battle nine other athletes for medals in the final.  Brume leapt to an automatic qualifying mark of 6.76m to book her spot in the final.  Usoro qualified with a mark of 6.68m, while she claimed her spot with 6.65m.  The final of the event will take place on Wednesday.  Transfer: Chelsea set to announce arrival of new striker for Maresca  Transfer: He's top, amazing player - Caicedo hails departing Chelsea star  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"